Hello @arsenm, 
This commit caused a performance regression of the benchmark we are tracking. Could you please have a look?

The reproducer is as follows (should be compiled w/ -O3):

```
#include <cmath>
double kernel(int64_t ibegin, int64_t iend,
                       double x0, double h,
                       double y, double xp, double yp)
{
    double sumx = 0.0;
    for (int64_t i = ibegin; i < iend; ++i) {
        double x = x0 + i * h;
        double denom = (x - xp)*(x - xp) + (y - yp)*(y - yp);
        denom = 1.0 / sqrt(denom);
        sumx += denom;
    }    
    return sumx;
}
```

This commit leads to the vectorization not beeing applied. Debug logs show the following message: 

```
LV: Not vectorizing: Found a non-intrinsic callsite 
```
On previous revision (12c89e40) this loop was successfully vectorized.

> Hello @arsenm, This commit caused a performance regression of the benchmark we are tracking. Could you please have a look?
> 
> The reproducer is as follows (should be compiled w/ -O3):
> 
> ```
> #include <cmath>
> double kernel(int64_t ibegin, int64_t iend,
>                        double x0, double h,
>                        double y, double xp, double yp)
> {
>     double sumx = 0.0;
>     for (int64_t i = ibegin; i < iend; ++i) {
>         double x = x0 + i * h;
>         double denom = (x - xp)*(x - xp) + (y - yp)*(y - yp);
>         denom = 1.0 / sqrt(denom);
>         sumx += denom;
>     }    
>     return sumx;
> }
> ```
> 
> This commit leads to the vectorization not beeing applied. Debug logs show the following message:
> 
> ```
> LV: Not vectorizing: Found a non-intrinsic callsite 
> ```
> 
> On previous revision (12c89e40) this loop was successfully vectorized.

It is because we cannot infer `x` is never an `undef` value. As a workaround, you can just wrap x with a function call to preserve `noundef` attribute: https://godbolt.org/z/czTozaz6K Perhaps we can fix it by handling recurrence PHI nodes in `isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison`.

Since we also observed performance degradation on other workloads https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/175166, I'd suggest reverting this commit in llvm 22's branch.
